Implemnted in snoop_section().


Types of TP input:
  1: TP without payload (AFC = 10)
  2: PUSI off (single continuing segment)
  3: PUSI on, ptr = 0 (start with new section or segment)
  4: PUSI on, ptr > 0 (start with ending segment)
     4a: the ending segment occupy the entire payload
     4b: the ending segment is following by STUFF byte (no more segment)
  5: subsequence starting segment in TP

4a and 4b are illegal cases, but need to be handled.


Snoop state:
  A: looking for new PSI section
  B: already started a PSI section


Processing:
  a: done with this TP (tp_ptr = NULL, return NULL)
  b: start a new PSI section (set snoop->sect, snoop->snooped_len)
  c: append to currnet PSI section (update snoop->snooped_len)
  d: finish a section (snoop->sect = NULL, return completed section)
  e: drop current section, and start a new one (error handling)


-------------------------------------

1A: a, OK
1B: a, OK
2A: a, OK
2B: c, OK
